Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo will meet in a mouthwatering clash in this season’s Champions League after Barcelona and Juventus were placed in the same group in Thursday’s draw. Messi and Ronaldo will resume the rivalry they developed when the Portuguese superstar was at Real Madrid. Between them they have won 11 of the last 12 Ballons d’Or. The two heavyweights were drawn in Group G along with Dynamo Kiev of Ukraine and Ferencvaros, the Hungarian club returning to the group stage for the first time in quarter of a century. Holders Bayern Munich will face Atletico Madrid, while Manchester United were drawn in the same group as Paris Saint-Germain and RB Leipzig, who met in last season’s semifinals. Liverpool were placed in a group which promises goals alongside Ajax and Atalanta as well as newboys FC Midtjylland, while Real Madrid and Inter Milan were also paired together in Group B. Elsewhere, Manchester City were drawn in the same group as Porto. Chelsea will face Europa League holders Sevilla. The group games will kick off Oct. 20 and 21 with the sixth games on Dec. 8 and 9 and the final in Istanbul’s Ataturk Stadium on May 29. Group stage draw in full: Group A: Bayern Munich, Atletico Madrid, Salzburg, Lokomotiv Moscow Group B: Real Madrid, Shakhtar Donetsk, Inter Milan, Borussia Monchengladbach Group C: Porto, Manchester City, Olympiakos, Marseille Group D: Liverpool, Ajax, Atalanta, Midtjylland Group E: Sevilla, Chelsea, FK Krasnodar, Rennes Group F: Zenit St Petersburg, Borussia Dortmund, Lazio, Bruges Group G: Juventus, Barcelona, Dynamo Kyiv, Ferencvaros Group H: Paris St-Germain, Manchester United, RB Leipzig, Istanbul Basaksehir